  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Listening Center for Women Survivors from GBV</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will establish a center (listen and support) for women and girls who are subjected to GBV, will provide specialized protection service through qualified staff consisting of the center&apos;s director and (4) social worker and lawyer. The Center will provide psychosocial support on a daily in the center, where there will be 4 social worker in the center to receive women inside the center, It will also provide legal support of judicial advice and representation by lawyer, for the women who need legal support. The center will be located in Al-Shahama Camp 1 in Salah al-Din Governorate

Listening center and psychosocial support will offer women a safe environment to help them build confidence and speak without fear and enable them to get their legal rights and to increase their knowledge of their rights and how to protect those rights through awareness workshops to be provided by staff of the center and dealing with concepts GBV, types of violence, and how to confront it from before them, and how to secure protection for themselves and their daughters in emergency situations.
The Center will also provide part of building confidence between it and survivors, (Specialized services) to help them overcome their difficult situation and reduce the risks they may face due to exploitation or harassment by camp service providers.
The Center will implement the psychosocial support activities, including workshops to teach women sewing and handmade.
The center will build, effective and active referral pathway in coordination with humanitarian agencies, UN agencies and other organisations working in the province and service departments and Hospital in the provincein order to facilitate intending to provide services to survivors and to ensure the speed and quality of the services.</narrative>
  </description>
